name: drive_files_generateIds
description: Generates a set of file IDs which can be provided in insert or copy requests.

maxResults.description: Maximum number of IDs to return.

space.description: The space in which the IDs can be used to create new files. Supported values are `drive` and `appDataFolder`. (Default: `drive`)

type.description: The type of items which the IDs can be used for. Supported values are `files` and `shortcuts`. Note that `shortcuts` are only supported in the `drive` `space`. (Default: `files`)

fields.description: Selector specifying which fields to include in a partial response.

key.description: API key. Your API key identifies your project and provides you with API access, quota, and reports. Required unless you provide an OAuth 2.0 token.

oauth_token.description: OAuth 2.0 token for the current user.

prettyPrint.description: Returns response with indentations and line breaks.

quotaUser.description: Available to use for quota purposes for server-side applications. Can be any arbitrary string assigned to a user, but should not exceed 40 characters.

$block: A list of generated IDs which can be provided in insert requests

$ul: **ids**: The IDs generated for the requesting user in the specified space.
**space**: The type of file that can be created with these IDs.
